es capex:** In Q1 2026, the AI segment accounted for **~76%** of total capital expenditures ($7,723M of $10,107M), up from ~62% in Q1 2025.\n2. **Accelerating trajectory:** Q1 2026 total capex of $10.1 billion already represents nearly **49% of FY 2025's full-year total** of $20.7 billion, signaling a significant step-up in spending pace.\n3. **AI infrastructure buildout:** The company notes it expects a **multi-year investment horizon** before AI deployments translate into sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA, and plans to allocate **substantial capital** to expand compute infrastructure.",
